Anh - Anh
moire
[mwα:]
(also moiré'mwα:reɪ)
■ noun silk subjected to heat and pressure after weaving to give a rippled appearance.
■ adjective (of silk) having a rippled finish.
⁃ having a pattern of wavy lines like that of moire.
Origin
C17: from Fr. moire 'mohair' (the original fabric); the var. moiré is from the past participle of moirer 'give a watered appearance'.

sentences.en: Swiss artist Milo Moire, 32, was slated by critics last year when she pushed paint-filled eggs out of her vagina.
sentences.vi: Nghệ sỹ này là Milo Moire, người Thụy Sỹ, 32 tuổi. Năm ngoái cô từng bị chỉ trích vì với hành động trình diễn màn đẻ trứng.
